    <stitle>PROPELLER SHAFT - OPERATION - CENTER (CARRIER) BEARING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CENTER (CARRIER) BEARING</title>
        <para>Center or carrier bearings (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0600104">Figure 4</hotlnk>) are designed to support long propeller shafts and to smooth out
            the delivery of power to the axle. The center (carrier) bearing used on International vehicles utilizes ball
            bearings with the bearing housing enclosed in rubber.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0600104" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0600104" filename="../figg06/G0600104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Center or Carrier Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
